akes\na world=\r\n move.\n    * When wanting to help, never think what the mans attitude shoul=\r\nd be\ntoward you.\n\n    * Ideal man is he who in midst of greatest silence fi=\r\nnds intensest\nactivity, and vice versa: the secret of restraint.\n\n    * Tam=\r\nas: inactivity\n\n    * Rajas: activity\n    * Sattva: calm, sweet, gentle, co=\r\nntrolling both T and R\n    * Plants, animal, men all governed by these 3 T,=\r\nR,S\n\n    * Karma yoga has to deal with these 3 elements\n\n    * Morality and=\r\n duty: according to mental constitution or the\ndifferent plane of existence=\r\n, duty and morality may vary. (There is no\nuniversal morality and duty).\n  =\r\n  * There are gradations of duty and morality: what is duty of one\nstate of=\r\n line in one set of circumstances will not be that of another.\n    * The ma=\r\nn who has begun to hate himself, the gate to degeneration has\nbeen opened!\n=\r\n    * To advance, we must have\n\n    *  faith in ourselves first (1) and\n\n  =\r\n  * then faith in God (2) and\n\n    * not hate our self.\n\n    * Two extremes=\r\n are very similar. (too low of light, or too bright:\nyou can&#39;t see)\n\n    * =\r\nLike was there is different in resistance (can strike, but do not)\nand non-=\r\nresistance ( can resist but do not)\n\n    * One who resist (not from weaknes=\r\ns, but willingly) commits a sin.\n\n    * Inactivity should be avoided by all=\r\n means. (tamas?)Activity means\nresistance.\n    * Until you&#39;ve passed throug=\r\nh that activity , (fulfill the desire)\nwill come the time when you know thi=\r\ns are little things, and you come to\nstate of calmness/serenity.\n    * Unit=\r\ny in variety is the plan of creation. (religion, caste,\nspecies)\n    * I sh=\r\nould not be judged by your standards, nor you be mine (apple to\napple compa=\r\nrison)\n    * Helping man\n\n    * spiritual knowledge is the highest help tha=\r\nt can be given to him.\n(give man a fish vs. teach to fish)\n    * Next to sp=\r\niri