tion.\n    * Duty is seldom sweet. Duty is sweet only th=\r\nrough love.\n    * A man should not be judged by nature of his duties but by=\r\n the\nmanner in which he does them.\n\n    * Our duty to others mean helping o=\r\nthers, doing good to the world.\nBut we really only help ourselves. This wor=\r\nld is not made that we should\ncome and help! World is perfect (normalized, =\r\nreached local/global\nmaxima), it is perfectly fitted to meet its ends. It d=\r\noes not need any\nhelp from us, Yet we must do good.\n\n    * Be grateful when=\r\n a helping opportunity arise! So that helping cause\n, you help yourself by =\r\nbeing good. It is the only way we can become\nperfect.\n    * Always remember=\r\n curly tail of dog when you have tendency to become\nfanatic. You need not w=\r\norry or make yourself sleepless, the world will\ngo on.\n    * It is level-he=\r\naded man, calm man of good judgment and cool nerves,\nof great sympathy and =\r\nlove, who does good work.\n    * (Same space/time) Good mind/thought, vs. ba=\r\nd mind/ thought resonate\neach other.. If you are tune to a frequency, someo=\r\nne broadcasting on\nthat frequency, you will pick that up.\n    * (Across tim=\r\ne) thought waves may travel hundreds of years until they\nmeet with an objec=\r\nt with which they vibrate in unison (resonance).\n    * When man is doing ev=\r\nil action, he has brought his mind to certain\nstate of tension (resonance )=\r\n, and all waves corresponding to that\ntension that are already in atmospher=\r\ne, will struggle to enter his mind!\nSo, this has two fold danger (receiver+=\r\n transmitter), first we open\nourselves to all the evil influences surroundi=\r\nng us; second we create\nsimilar waves which will affect others!!!\n\n    * Th=\r\ne action one has done cannot be destroyed unit it has borne\nfruit!\n\n    * A=\r\n perfect life is a contraction in terms. This compound struggle\nbetween som=\r\nething inside and external world is what we call life.\n    * The highest id=\r\neal is eternal and entire self-abnegation. Karma yoga\nleads to that.\n    * =\r\nPravritti (revolving towards you being the center: selfish) : evil\n(me my m=\r\nine)\n    * Nivritti (revolving away from me : selfless) : good .\n    * Self=\r\nishness is world, unselfishness is God.\n    * All actions bear good and evi=\r\nl at the same time! We cannot put a\nline of demarcation and say this action=\r\n is entirely good and this\nentirely evil. We cannot breathe or live without=\r\n injuring others.\n    * Any action that is not done for your own sake, what=\r\never it be, will\nhave no effect on you! Any action that you do for yourself=\r\n will bring an\neffect on you!\n\n    * Helping ourselves via Work\n\n    * Give=\r\n up idea of attachment (as an ordinary nurse, who take care of\nyour kid, bu=\r\nt walks away when done.)\n    * Do not mix in the fray: hold yourself as wit=\r\nness only!\n\n    * Give up fruits of work unto the lord\n    * The only duty =\r\nis to be unattached and to work as free beings\n\n    * Everything you do und=\r\ner compulsion is attachment\n\n    * Don&#39;t get attached. Its attachment comes=\r\n all our pain.\n\n    * Don&#39;t get pride in that someone is dependent upon you=\r\n.\n    * No-one in this universe depends upon us. They are all helped and\nwi=\r\nll be helped even if millions of us were not here.\n    * Helping other is a=\r\n privilege.\n\n    * World does not require any help from you. When you have =\r\ntrained\nyour nerves and your muscles to this idea, there will be no reactio=\r\nn in\nthe form of pain.\n    * Nothing in the universe has power over you unt=\r\nil you admit it.!!\n    * So by non-attachment, you deny the power of anythi=\r\nng to act upon\nyou.\n    * First hear, then think, and then practice. Practi=\r\nce is the key.\nMany things that you do not understand , by constant hearing=\r\n , will be\nmade clear.\n    * The explanation of everything is in yourself. =\r\nNo one was ever\